See my reply to Don for a more thorough analysis, Ron.  But to your point on
tire pressures, the shop originally set them to full pressure, which I
corrected promptly.

I will go a little further on the differential between tire setups.  The
Firestones were very large, wide and tall tires (-at-) 205/70HR14.  I think it's
a fair assumption that they would have different handling characteristics
from 185(/82)R14 as they are almost 11% wider wrt crosswinds.
